arts.ttl: Eredivisie: PSV Eindhoven go eight points clear as Van Persie battles relegation
arts.sum: PSV Eindhoven extended their lead at the top of the Eredivisie with a 2-1 away win over rivals AZ Alkmaar. Luuk de Jong and Noa Lang put the visitors two goals ahead after 21 minutes, although Denso Kasius’ late goal made for a nervy finish to the encounter. arts.ttl: FC Twente 1-3 Chelsea: Player ratings as Blues extend Champions League winning streak
arts.sum: The Blues dominated the ball for much of the first half, with summer signing and France international Sandy Baltimore particularly impressive on the left wing, and their superiority was rewarded with a second goal just over ten minutes later. Still riding high after their London derby win over Arsenal in the WSL, the Blues proved once again why they are worthy contenders for the champions of Europe crown, coasting to victory thanks to goals from Aggie Beever-Jones, Maika Hamano and Guro Reiten.

arts.ttl: Chelsea cruise past Twente as Bompastor maintains perfect start
arts.sum: Sonia Bompastor continued her 100 per cent record since taking charge at Chelsea as her side beat Twente 3-1 to secure a second Women's Champions League win of the season.
